	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 28th 6:10 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some of these posts show such ignorance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sure, to us uber d00ds this robe sucks.  But to a lvl 10 chanter non-twink (without a high level alt), this is well worth saving up a few thousand CP and SP for.  There are still plenty of people new to EQ and will pay decent prices for decent armor.  Not everyone has a lv59 main who can farm stuff for all his alts.<br><br>It reminded me of hunting in PAW and watching people letting the split-paw stuff just rot away.  To newbies, the split-paw armor is wonderful, and well worth the 10-20pp they will offer (and can afford) for it.<br><br>If you don't believe me, try this:<br><br>Go into the EC-mart and auction stuff saying "NEWBIE ITEMS- 100pp and below..."  I guarantee that you will get a zillion tells from the little ones.  You'll feel like an ass for all the times you dumped lowbie armor as worthless.  Then sit back and watch the same 15 people auctioning their Fungis for the last 836365 hours.<br><br>Selling lowbie stuff is better than giving it away as people will feel like they accomplished something when they work for it.  I never give stuff away for nothing.  At the very least, I create small player-events for newbies to earn the stuff.  Even fetching me a stack of spider legs for a velium sword makes the game fun for both parties.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ardnahoy<br>Noble Cavalier of the 51st Crusade<br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
